        <div class="mx-5 fs-5 pt-3" style="text-align: justify;">
            <p>The RMO Director has the following key task responsibilities: 1) assists in the implementation of policies in research, and development programs of the university; 2) prioritizes research programs that have significant impact and contribution to the University's attainment of globally competitive education, improvement of the quality of life an social development; 3) conducts institutional researches that would address efficiency and effectiveness of the services offered by the university to its stakeholders and the larger community; 4) provides administrative and technical support to university researchers and faculty members to harness their research capability  and skills; 5) supervises the operation of the Research Support Center; Research Monitoring and Evaluation Center, Center for Research Dissemination and Linkages, and Center for Research Ethics; 6) undertakes evaluative studies covering students and faculty sectors; 7) provides technical assistance in the preparation of research designs and in the collection, processing, analyzing, and interpreting of research data to faculty students; 8) implements policies of the University relative to planned institutional research alignment; 9) undertakes institutional researches and evaluative studies covering various sectors in the university; 10) undertakes preparation of feasibility and other studies of the university; 11) collates, evaluates, and interprets institutional statistical information to the university, domestic and international use; 12) prepares programs designed towards the development of true international relations and understanding; 13) establishes and maintains linkages with international organizations of similar education goals to facilitate research and student-faculty exchange programs; 14) establishes and maintains linkages with national institutions with similar educational goals to facilitate the conduct of various researches contributing to national understanding; and 15) submits reports to the management.</p>
